.SS FILTER
.PP
Create a new handle on the array with a subset of rows, as determined
by a callback function.
.PP
.proto_filter
.RS 7
.arg_handle
.TP
.I selector_callback
is a script function that will be called with each row of the source
handle.
The callback function will receive two arguments, an array name to be
used with a nameref variable, and an integer row number that will
almost always be ignored.
Return 0 to keep the row, 1 (or other non-zero) to discard the row.
.TP
.I new_handle_name
is the name to use for the new handle if the filtering succeeded.
.TP
.RI [ ... ]
optional extra arguments, as needed, to be transmitted to the
.I selector_callback
function for each row.
.RE
.TP
.B Selector Callback Function
The
.B selector_callback
script function will be called for each row of the table to determine
whether or not the row should be included in the filtered table.
.IP
The
.I selector_callback
function will be called with the following arguments:
.TS
tab(|);
l lx.
\(Do1|T{
.B row's contents
have been copied to an array whose name is in the
.I $1
argument.
T}
\&....|T{
.B extra arguments
passed to the \fBfilter\fP action.
T}
.TE
.IP
Return zero (0) if the row should be included in the filtered list,
and a non-zero value to refuse the row.
